title: Places I've Lived
name: Places I've Lived
description:
A Map by Silusgrok

Um... this is a list of all the cities I've lived in ( though not all the addresses I've lived at — hey, I've gotta keep some things private )!

properties.name: City of Québec (Ville de Québec), Québec, Canada
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokQuebec City, Quebec, CANADAOne of the oldest walled cities in North America, Québec City is also the cultural heart of French Canada.

properties.name: Clovis, CA
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokClovis, California is a charming township situated between the City of Fresno, and the Sierra Nevada mountains. It has suffered, recently — as has the rest of the San Joaquin Valley — the ravaging of sprawl-frenzied developers and acquiescent city governments.

properties.name: Gatineau, Québec, Canada
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokGatineau, Québec, CanadaGatineau is a large French-speaking city across the Ottawa River (and thus, across the provincial border) from Canada\'s capital, Ottawa Ontario.

properties.name: Huntington Lake, CA
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokAn idyllic high-Sierra community found along state highway 168 in Fresno county.

properties.name: Montreal, QC
properties.description: Posted by ObuchMontreal

properties.name: Provo, UT
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokProvo, UTProvo is a town of some 110 thousand people located along the beautiful Provo River, between the south-central Wasatch mountains and Utah Lake. It is home to Brigham Young University.

properties.name: Repentigny, Québec, Canada
properties.description: Posted by Silusgrokrepentigny, québecA quiet hamlet just North and East of the island of Hochelaga — and it\'s most famous city, Montréal. Repentigny is a middle-class enclave just over the river from, and out of sight of the choking industrialism of the eastern banlieus of Montréal. It is part of a sisterhood of charming townships that constitute Montréal\'s North Shore / Le Rive Nord.

properties.name: Saint-Eustache, Québec, Canada
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokSaint-Eustache is a suburb of Montréal, Québec.

properties.name: Saint-Jean-sur-Richeliue, Québec, Canada
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokSaint-Jean is a small agricultural town within earshot of the City of Montréal, but worlds apart. It is the gateway to the Eastern Townships and to the fertile farmland of Southern Québec.

properties.name: Salt Lake City, UT
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokSalt Lake City, UT The greater Salt Lake City area is home to 1.5 million people, and recently played host to the 2002 Winter Olympics. It is the financial and cultural center of the Great Basin and inter-mountain West. Salt Lake City is also home to the world headquarters of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints — which plays a significant role in shaping the culture of the region.

properties.name: Spokane Valley, WA
properties.description: Posted by SilusgrokSpokane Valley, WA, United StatesLocated East of the City of Spokane, Spokane Valley is a newly-incorporated city comprised of a large part of Spokane County, WA.
